Subject: [PATCH] Disable pipe2 detection on Apple platforms

CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX is a link-only test. Starting with Xcode 26 /
iOS Simulator 26.4 SDK the `pipe2` symbol is present in libsystem so the
link succeeds, but `pipe2` is not declared in any system header for the
deployment targets we use (e.g. iOS 13). Apple Clang now treats implicit
function declarations as a hard error, so evutil.c fails to compile.

Skip the detection on Apple — libevent already has a `pipe()` fallback
gated by `#if defined(EVENT__HAVE_PIPE2)`.
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -454,7 +454,9 @@
 CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX(kqueue EVENT__HAVE_KQUEUE)
 CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX(mmap EVENT__HAVE_MMAP)
 CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX(pipe EVENT__HAVE_PIPE)
-CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX(pipe2 EVENT__HAVE_PIPE2)
+if(NOT APPLE)
+    CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX(pipe2 EVENT__HAVE_PIPE2)
+endif()
 CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX(poll EVENT__HAVE_POLL)
 CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX(port_create EVENT__HAVE_PORT_CREATE)
 CHECK_FUNCTION_EXISTS_EX(sendfile EVENT__HAVE_SENDFILE)
